(82, 31, 1, 'https://www.theverge.com/news/803373/microsoft-windows-11-emergency-update-usb-mouse-keyboard-recovery-environment-issues', 'Microsoft’s emergency Windows 11 update fixes a nasty system recovery bug', 'Microsoft is now rolling out an out-of-band fix for Windows 11 to address a major bug the company introduced with its latest monthly Windows 11 update. The original update released on October 14th accidentally broke the Windows Recovery Environment (WinRE), l…', '<ul><li></li><li></li><li></li></ul>\r\nThis update fixes a problem with the Windows Recovery Environment not working with a USB mouse or keyboard.\r\nThis update fixes a problem with the Windows Recover… [+2074 chars]', 'https://www.theverge.com/news/803373/microsoft-windows-11-emergency-update-usb-mouse-keyboard-recovery-environment-issues', 'https://platform.theverge.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/STK109_WINDOWS_C.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C10.732984293194%2C100%2C78.534031413613&w=1200', '2025-10-21 21:03:24', '{\"source\":{\"id\":\"the-verge\",\"name\":\"The Verge\"},\"author\":\"Tom Warren\",\"title\":\"Microsoft\\u2019s emergency Windows 11 update fixes a nasty system recovery bug\",\"description\":\"Microsoft is now rolling out an out-of-band fix for Windows 11 to address a major bug the company introduced with its latest monthly Windows 11 update. The original update released on October 14th accidentally broke the Windows Recovery Environment (WinRE), l\\u2026\",\"url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.theverge.com\\/news\\/803373\\/microsoft-windows-11-emergency-update-usb-mouse-keyboard-recovery-environment-issues\",\"urlToImage\":\"https:\\/\\/platform.theverge.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/2\\/2025\\/02\\/STK109_WINDOWS_C.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&crop=0%2C10.732984293194%2C100%2C78.534031413613&w=1200\",\"publishedAt\":\"2025-10-21T14:03:24Z\",\"content\":\"<ul><li><\\/li><li><\\/li><li><\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\nThis update fixes a problem with the Windows Recovery Environment not working with a USB mouse or keyboard.\\r\\nThis update fixes a problem with the Windows Recover\\u2026 [+2074 chars]\"}', '2025-11-10 01:15:17', '2025-11-10 08:16:34', NULL),
