sed injury reports, including references to \\u201csoreness\\u201d, to estimate menstrual cycles. Give it some time, however, and perhaps they\\u2019ll start hacking commercial period tracking apps, many of which already leak sensitive user data. Earlier this year, for example, a federal jury found that Meta violated the California Invasion of Privacy Act by collecting data from Flo, a popular period tracking app, without user consent. While period cycle betting is invasive and creepy, these gamblers aren\\u2019t entirely off-base in their reasoning: your menstrual cycle can have an impact on your athletic performance. Indeed, researchers at University College London just published a study that found female athletes have faster reaction times during ovulation. Perhaps, if we\\u2019re looking for silver linings, there is some positive benefit to men getting interested in luteal phases and women\\u2019s hormone levels. Perhaps if we get enough gamblers deciding there is money to be made from this, we\\u2019ll see more resources go towards women\\u2019s health, which is chronically underfunded? Humour me here: I\\u2019m trying to be positive. It\\u2019s difficult, but I\\u2019m trying. If we are really trying to look on the bright side, the rise of period betting points to just how popular women\\u2019s sports are becoming. Women\\u2019s football, for example, already one of the top 10 most followed sports globally, is on track to become one of the top five sports by 2030, according to Nielsen Sports. And, halfway through the 2025 season, WNBA ratings are breaking records and drawing in a broader fanbase. The New York Times reports that the number of boys under 18 who watch WNBA has grown by 130% over the past four years. Whenever women are in the spotlight, though, there are people who punish them for it. The joy and excitement of the Women\\u2019s World Cup in 2023, for example, was overshadowed by Luis Rubiales, the former president of the Spanish Football Federation, kissing Spain forward Jenni Hermoso on the lips without her consent. It \\u201cstained one of the happiest days of my life\\u201d, Hermoso said at the time. And there was a record number of reports of abuse at matches in English football during the 2024-25 season, according to data from Kick It Out; complaints of misogyny and sexism drove this increase. Whether it\\u2019s sexist chants, dildo tossing or period cycle betting, the world is full of small men desperate to spoil a woman\\u2019s big moment. \\u2022 Arwa Mahdawi is a Guardian columnist Do you have an opinion on the issues raised in this article? If you would like to submit a response of up to 300 words by email to be considered for publication in our letters section, please click here.\",\"charCount\":\"4671\",\"shouldHideReaderRevenue\":\"false\",\"showAffiliateLinks\":\"false\",\"bylineHtml\":\"<a href=\\\"profile\\/arwa-mahdawi\\\">Arwa Mahdawi<\\/a>\"},\"isHosted\":false,\"pillarId\":\"pillar\\/opinion\",\"pillarName\":\"Opinion\"}', '2025-11-10 01:15:26', '2025-11-10 01:15:26', NULL);
