(109, NULL, NULL, 'media/2025/oct/30/lachlan-murdoch-top-adviser-siobhan-mckenna-resigns-from-news-corp', 'Lachlan Murdoch’s top adviser Siobhan McKenna resigns from News Corp', 'Company’s Australian broadcast chief, who was involved in negotiations over Murdoch family’s succession plans, to depart media giant', 'Lachlan Murdoch’s top adviser – News Corp’s Australian broadcasting chief Siobhan McKenna – has resigned from the company following the sale of the Foxtel Group to global sports streaming service DAZN. As chief executive of broadcasting for News Corp, McKenna’s role had significantly diminished after the pay TV and streaming business, which includes Kayo, Binge and Hubbl, was sold to the European broadcaster in April. A former partner at McKinsey &amp; Company, McKenna was Murdoch’s key adviser in the epic family trust case, which saw him take control of his father’s global media empire and secure the future of the Australian stable of newspapers, magazines and news channels. The 53-year-old businessperson was heavily involved in the negotiations with Rupert Murdoch’s three “objecting children” in the Nevada court case, which was settled in the US last month. The three oldest siblings received an estimated US$1.1bn each for their shares in the business. Sign up: AU Breaking News email McKenna will leave the company at the end of the year, staff were told by News Corp’s global chief executive, Robert Thomson, in an email on Thursday morning. “Her decision, and it is her decision, is essentially epochal as Siobhan has been a transformational force during her years with News Corp,” Thomson said. “The word ‘visionary’ is often abused, but not in Siobhan’s case, as her ability to perceive the future from the haze-shrouded shapes on the horizon is nonpareil. She is irreplaceable.” McKenna and Lachlan set up the private investment company Illyria 20 years ago, having both great success with Nova Entertainment and significant losses when he took over the Ten network in 2012 before it went into voluntary administration in 2017. The Albanese government appointed McKenna as chair of Australia Post in 2022, citing her commercial, strategic, digital and technology experience. Thomson said McKenna navigated Sky News Australia and Foxtel through a “treacherous tech landscape” and made them into “global success stories”. “The worth of Foxtel was instinctively appreciated by the global leader in sports streaming, DAZN, which recently acquired the company, and with whom we have an ongoing partnership,” he said. “Sky was transformed from a traditional broadcaster to a digital powerhouse whose efficacious impact stretches far beyond the borders of Australia. The success of both companies marks a profound turning point for our company and a professional inflexion point for Siobhan.” Lachlan is the chair of News Corp, the parent company of more than two dozen publications including the Wall Street Journal, The Times and the New York Post, after he succeeded his father in 2023 and executive chair and CEO of Fox Corporation.', 'https://www.theguardian.com/media/2025/oct/30/lachlan-murdoch-top-adviser-siobhan-mckenna-resigns-from-news-corp', 'https://media.guim.co.uk/43497f8f487bb3db9791c2b65280faec40d8c394/732_0_3473_2780/500.jpg', '2025-10-30 07:45:53', '{\"id\":\"media\\/2025\\/oct\\/30\\/lachlan-murdoch-top-adviser-siobhan-mckenna-resigns-from-news-corp\",\"type\":\"article\",\"sectionId\":\"media\",\"sectionName\":\"Media\",\"webPublicationDate\":\"2025-10-30T00:45:53Z\",\"webTitle\":\"Lachlan Murdoch\\u2019s top adviser Siobhan McKenna resigns from News Corp\",\"webUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/www.theguardian.com\\/media\\/2025\\/oct\\/30\\/lachlan-murdoch-top-adviser-siobhan-mckenna-resigns-from-news-corp\",\"apiUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/content.guardianapis.com\\/media\\/2025\\/oct\\/30\\/lachlan-murdoch-top-adviser-siobhan-mckenna-resigns-from-news-corp\",\"fields\":{\"headline\":\"Lachlan Murdoch\\u2019s top adviser Siobhan McKenna resigns from News Corp\",\"standfirst\":\"<p>Company\\u2019s Australian broadcast chief, who was involved in negotiations over Murdoch family\\u2019s succession plans, to depart media giant<\\/p><ul><li><p><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.theguardian.com\\/australia-news\\/live\\/2025\\/oct\\/30\\/anthony-albanese-donald-trump-meeting-murray-watt-epbc-nature-laws-press-club-parliament-labor-coalition-sussan-ley-ntwnfb\\\">Follow our Australia news live blog for latest updates<\\/a><\\/p><\\/li><li><p>Get our <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.theguardian.com\\/email-newsletters?CMP=cvau_sfl\\\">breaking news email<\\/a>, <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/app.adjust.com\\/w4u7jx3\\\">free app<\\/a> or <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.theguardian.com\\/australia-news\\/series\\/full-story?CMP=cvau_sfl\\\">daily news podcast<\\/a><\\/p><\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"trailText\":\"Company\\u2019s Australian broadcast chief, who was involved in negotiations over Murdoch family\\u2019s succession plans, to depart media giant\",\"byline\":\"Amanda Meade\",\"main\":\"<figure class=\\\"element element-image\\\" data-media-id=\\\"43497f8f487bb3db9791c2b65280faec40d8c394\\\"> <img src=\\\"https:\\/\\/media.guim.co.uk\\/43497f8f487bb3db9791c2b65280faec40d8c394\\/0_0_5005_3478\\/1000.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"Foxtel\\u2019s Siobhan McKenna speaking at an AFL event in 2022.\\\" width=\\\"1000\\\" height=\\\"695\\\" class=\\\"gu-image\\\" \\/> <figcaption> <span class=\\\"element-image__caption\\\">Siobhan McKenna speaking at an AFL event in 2022. News Corp\\u2019s global boss Robert Thomson has told staff that McKenna \\u2013 a key adviser to Lachlan Murdoch \\u2013 will leave the company at the end of the year.<\\/span> <span class=\\\"element-image__credit\\\">Photograph: Quinn Rooney\\/Getty Images<\\/span> <\\/figcaption> <\\/figure>\",\"body\":\"<p>Lachlan Murdoch\\u2019s top adviser \\u2013 News Corp\\u2019s Australian broadcasting chief Siobhan McKenna \\u2013 has resigned from the company following the sale of the Foxtel Group to global sports streaming service DAZN.<\\/p> <p>As chief executive of broadcasting for News Corp, McKenna\\u2019s role had significantly diminished after <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.theguardian.com\\/media\\/2024\\/dec\\/23\\/news-corp-and-telstra-agree-sale-of-foxtel-to-sports-streaming-service-dazn-for-us22bn\\\">the pay TV<\\/a> and streaming business, which includes Kayo, Binge and Hubbl, was sold to the European broadcaster in April.<\\/p> <p>A former partner at McKinsey &amp; Company, McKenna was <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.theguardian.com\\/media\\/2025\\/sep\\/09\\/lachlan-murdoch-news-corp-media-succession-australian-newspapers\\\">Murdoch\\u2019s key adviser<\\/a> in the epic family trust case, which saw him take control of his father\\u2019s global media empire and secure the future of the Australian stable of newspapers, magazines and news channels.<\\/p> <p>The 53-year-old businessperson was heavily involved in the negotiations with Rupert Murdoch\\u2019s three \\u201cobjecting children\\u201d in the Nevada court case, which was <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.theguardian.com\\/us-news\\/2025\\/sep\\/08\\/rupert-murdoch-lachlan-family-succession-deal\\\">settled in the US last month<\\/a>. The three oldest siblings received an estimated US$1.1bn each for their shares in the business.<\\/p> <p><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.theguardian.com\\/email-newsletters?CMP=copyembed&amp;CMP=emailbutton\\\"><sub>Sign up: AU Breaking News email<\\/sub><\\/a><\\/p> <p>McKenna will leave the company at the end of the year, staff were told by News Corp\\u2019s global chief executive, Robert Thomson, in an email on Thursday morning.<\\/p> <p>\\u201cHer decision, and it is her decision, is essentially epochal as Siobhan has been a transformational force during her years with News Corp,\\u201d Thomson said.<\\/p> <p>\\u201cThe word \\u2018visionary\\u2019 is often abused, but not in Siobhan\\u2019s case, as her ability to perceive the future from the haze-shrouded shapes on the horizon is nonpareil. She is irreplaceable.\\u201d<\\/p>    <p>McKenna and Lachlan set up the private investment company Illyria 20 years ago, having both great success with Nova Entertainment and significant losses when he took over the Ten network in 2012 before it went into <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.theguardian.com\\/media\\/2017\\/sep\\/18\\/lachlan-murdoch-and-bruce-gordon-lose-court-bid-to-stop-sale-of-network-ten-to-cbs\\\">voluntary administration in 2017<\\/a>.<\\/p> <p>The Albanese government appointed McKenna as chair of Australia Post in 2022, citing her commercial, strategic, digital and technology experience.<\\/p> <p>Thomson said McKenna navigated Sky News Australia and Foxtel through a \\u201ctreacherous tech landscape\\u201d and made them into \\u201cglobal success stories\\u201d.<\\/p> <p>\\u201cThe worth of Foxtel was instinctively appreciated by the global leader in sports streaming, DAZN, which recently acquired the company, and with whom we have an ongoing partnership,\\u201d he said.<\\/p> <p>\\u201cSky was transformed from a traditional broadcaster to a digital powerhouse whose efficacious impact stretches far beyond the borders of Australia. The success of both companies marks a profound turning point for our company and a professional inflexion point for Siobhan.\\u201d<\\/p> <p>Lachlan is the chair of News Corp, the parent company of more than two dozen publications including the Wall Street Journal, The Times and the New York Post, after he succeeded his father in 2023 and executive chair and CEO of Fox Corporation.<\\/p>  <figure class=\\\"element element-embed\\\" data-alt=\\\"pointer\\\">  <iframe class=\\\"fenced\\\" srcdoc=\\\"&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;\\/head&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;script src=&quot;https:\\/\\/uploads.guim.co.uk\\/2025\\/01\\/21\\/article-button.js&quot;&gt;&lt;script&gt;&lt;\\/body&gt;&lt;\\/html&gt;\\\"><\\/iframe> <\\/figure>\",\"wordcount\":\"433\",\"firstPublicationDate\":\"2025-10-30T00:45:53Z\",\"isInappropriateForSponsorship\":\"false\",\"isPremoderated\":\"false\",\"lastModified\":\"2025-10-30T01:17:54Z\",\"productionOffice\":\"AUS\",\"publication\":\"theguardian.com\",\"shortUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/www.theguardian.com\\/p\\/x3hh9j\",\"shouldHideAdverts\":\"false\",\"showInRelatedContent\":\"true\",\"thumbnail\":\"https:\\/\\/media.guim.co.uk\\/43497f8f487bb3db9791c2b65280faec40d8c394\\/732_0_3473_2780\\/500.jpg\",\"legallySensitive\":\"false\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"isLive\":\"true\",\"bodyText\":\"Lachlan Murdoch\\u2019s top adviser \\u2013 News Corp\\u2019s Australian broadcasting chief Siobhan McKenna \\u2013 has resigned from the company following the sale of the Foxtel Group to global sports streaming service DAZN. As chief executive of broadcasting for News Corp, McKenna\\u2019s role had significantly diminished after the pay TV and streaming business, which includes Kayo, Binge and Hubbl, was sold to the European broadcaster in April. A former partner at McKinsey &amp; Company, McKenna was Murdoch\\u2019s key adviser in the epic family trust case, which saw him take control of his father\\u2019s global media empire and secure the future of the Australian stable of newspapers, magazines and news channels. The 53-year-old businessperson was heavily involved in the negotiations with Rupert Murdoch\\u2019s three \\u201cobjecting children\\u201d in the Nevada court case, which was settled in the US last month. The three oldest siblings received an estimated US$1.1bn each for their shares in the business. Sign up: AU Breaking News email McKenna will leave the company at the end of the year, staff were told by News Corp\\u2019s global chief executive, Robert Thomson, in an email on Thursday morning. \\u201cHer decision, and it is her decision, is essentially epochal as Siobhan has been a transformational force during her years with News Corp,\\u201d Thomson said. \\u201cThe word \\u2018visionary\\u2019 is often abused, but not in Siobhan\\u2019s case, as her ability to perceive the future from the haze-shrouded shapes on the horizon is nonpareil. She is irreplaceable.\\u201d McKenna and Lachlan set up the private investment company Illyria 20 years ago, having both great success with Nova Entertainment and significant losses when he took over the Ten network in 2012 before it went into voluntary administration in 2017. The Albanese government appointed McKenna as chair of Australia Post in 2022, citing her commercial, strategic, digital and technology experience. Thomson said McKenna navigated Sky News Australia and Foxtel through a \\u201ctreacherous tech landscape\\u201d and made them into \\u201cglobal success stories\\u201d. \\u201cThe worth of Foxtel was instinctively appreciated by the global leader in sports streaming, DAZN, which recently acquired the company, and with whom we have an ongoing partnership,\\u201d he said. \\u201cSky was transformed from a traditional broadcaster to a digital powerhouse whose efficacious impact stretches far beyond the borders of Australia. The success of both companies marks a profound turning point for our company and a professional inflexion point for Siobhan.\\u201d Lachlan is the chair of News Corp, the parent company of more than two dozen publications including the Wall Street Journal, The Times and the New York Post, after he succeeded his father in 2023 and executive chair and CEO of Fox Corporation.\",\"charCount\":\"2750\",\"shouldHideReaderRevenue\":\"false\",\"showAffiliateLinks\":\"false\",\"bylineHtml\":\"<a href=\\\"profile\\/amanda-meade\\\">Amanda Meade<\\/a>\",\"showTableOfContents\":\"false\"},\"isHosted\":false,\"pillarId\":\"pillar\\/news\",\"pillarName\":\"News\"}', '2025-11-10 01:15:26', '2025-11-10 01:15:26', NULL),
(110, NULL, NULL, 'sport/2025/oct/24/premier-league-team-news-predicted-lineups-for-the-weekend-action', 'Premier League team news: predicted lineups for the weekend action', 'Champions Liverpool pay a visit to Brentford on Saturday night while leaders Arsenal host Crystal Palace on Sunday', 'CHELSEA v SUNDERLAND Saturday 3pm Venue Stamford Bridge Referee Andy Madley This season G1 Y5 R0 5.0 cards/game Chelsea Subs from Slonina, Jörgensen, Hato, Adarabioyo, Fofana, Lavia, Santos, Buonanotte, Estêvão, George, Mheuka, Garnacho, Walsh Doubtful None Injured Delap (hamstring, 1 Nov), Palmer (groin, 3 Dec), Badiashile (muscle, 3 Dec), Colwill (knee, unknown), Essugo (thigh, unknown) Suspended Gusto (one match), Mudryk (indefinite) Form WDLLWW Leading scorers Caicedo, Fernández 3 Sunderland Subs from Patterson, Geertruida, Masuaku, Neil, O’Nien, Traoré, Brobbey, Adingra, Mayenda Doubtful Sadiki (ankle) Injured Alderete (concussion, 3 Nov), Cirkin (wrist, 3 Nov), Mundle (hamstring, 22 Nov), Diarra (groin, Dec) Suspended None Form WDDWLW Leading scorer Isidor 3 *** NEWCASTLE v FULHAM Saturday 3pm Venue St James’ Park Referee Tony Harrington This season G4 Y17 R0 4.25 cards/game Newcastle Subs from Ramsdale, Schär, Krafth, Lascelles, Miley, Willock, Ramsey, Barnes, Elanga, Osula Doubtful Tonali (illness) Injured Hall (hamstring, 8 Nov), Livramento (knee, 22 Nov), Wissa (knee, Dec) Suspended None Form DWDLWL Leading scorer Woltemade 4 Fulham Subs from Lecomte, Tete, Cuenca, Reed, Cairney, Smith Rowe, Kevin, Traoré, Kusi-Asare Doubtful Lukic (groin), Cairney (back) Injured Muniz (hamstring, 1 Nov), Robinson (knee, unknown), Chukwueze (calf, unknown), Andersen (hamstring, unknown) Suspended None Form LWWLLL Leading scorers Iwobi, Jiménez, Muniz, Sessegnon, Smith Rowe, Wilson 1 *** MANCHESTER UTD v BRIGHTON Saturday 5.30pm Sky Sports Premier League Venue Old Trafford Referee Anthony Taylor This season G7 Y18 R0 2.57 cards/game Manchester Utd Subs from Bayindir, Heaton, Mee, Frede